From: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
Subject: [PATCH] nss_data_plane: fix rmmod panic on double unregister

__nss_data_plane_unregister() walks every core's subsys_dp table, but each
physical interface is registered to all cores. The first unregister clears
nss_data_plane_params[i].nss_ctx; the second pass can feed NULL into the HAL
unregister path.

Unregister from nss-dp only on the first pass.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
---
 nss_data_plane/nss_data_plane.c | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/nss_data_plane/nss_data_plane.c
+++ b/nss_data_plane/nss_data_plane.c
@@ -347,7 +347,14 @@ static void __nss_data_plane_unregister(
 	for (core = 0; core < nss_top_main.num_nss; core++) {
 		for (i = NSS_DP_START_IFNUM; i < NSS_DP_MAX_INTERFACES; i++) {
 			if (nss_top_main.nss[core].subsys_dp_register[i].ndev) {
-				nss_data_plane_unregister_from_nss_dp(i);
+				/*
+				 * The same interface is registered to every
+				 * core's subsys_dp table; unregister from
+				 * nss-dp only once or the second pass feeds
+				 * a NULLed nss_ctx to the hal unregister.
+				 */
+				if (nss_data_plane_params[i].nss_ctx)
+					nss_data_plane_unregister_from_nss_dp(i);
 				nss_core_unregister_subsys_dp(&nss_top_main.nss[core], i);
 			}
 		}
